{
  "stem": "4361.8",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then, as I said, I had about two weeks of-- of what would be considered-- because I just didn't want to get out of bed, and I just lay there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I didn't want to see anybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I couldn't cry, and that was the worst.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I-- I was just laying there and I really believed that Stern, Milikah is making up these stories.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "No, my-- he'll-- he'll come home someday, somehow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Eventually, after two weeks, some of my friends came and said, look, Barbara, there is the Joint, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We are-- let's see what we can do.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They pulled me out, and I went to the Joint and the Joint was very-- very-- very supportive, very supportive.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then, I went back to see my parents' house, and that was a horrible experience.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "All the windows and the doors were ripped out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The parquet floor was ripped up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "People were-- have-- not only did they loot and empty the house of furniture and everything, but they also pulled up, as I said, the parquet floors to see if we didn't hide something.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Because they knew that Fischman was a fairly wealthy man and things-- you know, the Jew hid things.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So I couldn't live there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "By this time, my sister-- sister-in-law and of course, my other sister-in-law was very close to me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I knew both my brothers did not survive, so it seemed to me at that time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And my then sister-in-law, this Lajchu, her family's house was fairly intact because this Milikah Stern who was liberated in Buchenwald in April, he somehow managed to come home very, very soon thereafter, and he found his house, his parents' house.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He even, I was told, did something which he shouldn't have done.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
